data.title: Plano Symphony Orchestra
data.meta_description: For more information, or to make your pledge now, please contact:
data.text:
• TWO tables / up to SIXTEEN seats at the annual Virtuoso Dinner (typically held in May/June)

• Naming rights to a musician chair or section of your choice (depending on availability) for the duration of your pledge (first come, first served; subject to availability)

• Recognition on PSO website, in concert programs, and from the stage at one concert each season

• Private lunch with the Maestro and/or Assistant Conductor

• Behind-the-scenes access to TWO (2) select concert rehearsals during the season

• Invitation to ALL post-concert receptions, including a Virtuoso Society-exclusive post-concert event with the Maestro

• Host a couple guests at a PSO concert (unlimited – requires advance reservations)

• ONE table / up to EIGHT seats at the annual Virtuoso Dinner (typically held in May/June)

• Naming rights to a musician chair or section of your choice (depending on availability) for the duration of your pledge (first come, first served; subject to availability)

• Recognition on PSO website, in concert programs, and from the stage at one concert each season

• Behind-the-scenes access to ONE select concert rehearsal during the season

• Invitation to a Virtuoso Society-exclusive post-concert event with the Maestro

• Host a couple guests at a PSO concert (unlimited – requires advance reservations)

• FOUR tickets (4) to the annual Virtuoso Dinner (typically held in May/June)

• Recognition on PSO website and in concert programs

• Host a couple guests at a PSO concert (unlimited – requires advance reservations)

• Invitation to a Virtuoso Society-exclusive post-concert event with the Maestro

• Attendance at one rehearsal during the season

• Invitation to a private post-concert reception with the Maestro

• TWO tickets (2) to the annual Virtuoso Dinner (typically held in May/June)

• Recognition on PSO website and in concert programs

• Host a couple guests at a PSO concert (one time – requires advance reservations)

• Invitation to a Virtuoso Society-exclusive post-concert event with the Maestro
